Hi @bernhardreiter,

> What are the differences to https://github.com/tk0miya/testing.postgresql especially when would one use the one or the other?

To be frank, I've never seen this project before, which means that I can't provide a concrete answer to this question. We strive to create a tool that's suitable for us. However, here's an approximate list of testgres' features:

- Aims to look like TAP tests framework provided by PostgreSQL;
- Connection wrapper object (`begin()`, `commit()`, `abort()`, set transaction isolation level);
- Configurable node builder (data directory, various configs, node's name etc);
- It's easy to set up a hot standby / cluster etc;
